title: PML-N candidate Zarak Khan wins PB-42 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Zarak Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-42, Quetta-V by securing 10,423 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Hazara Democratic Party candidate Abdul Khaliq who bagged 8,520 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 24 per cent.
